title: For Sale:  Taurus 608 BEATER + ammo  PICS ADDED AND PRICE REDUCED!!!
postcontent:
Taurus 608 .357 magnum.

8 round cylinder, target sights, ported barrel, heavyweight X-frame.

UGLY gun. Previous owner took it on camping trips in the mountains and fired hot handloads out of it. It is beat to hell. Then he did a botched cold bluing job to cover up some of the scratches and scuffs. It is UGLY and it is loose but it is safe to shoot and incredibly accurate. I've fired 150 rounds with no issues whatsoever.

Timing is perfect. Lockup at full cock is solid. Forcing cone looks fine. Outstanding DA trigger pull. Great sights. Heavy frame and ported barrel means minimal recoil.

I bought this piece last year for $300. I am asking 275 and will throw in a brand new shoulder holster (left handed) and 265 rounds of factory .357 FREE.

Ammo is: 10 rds of Black Talon
25 rds Hornaday 140 gr FTX
20 rds 158 gr Speer Gold Dot
10 rds 125 gr Hydra Shok
50 rds Federal 125 gr Hi-Shok
100 rds Winchester 158 gr JHP
50 rds Federal truncated lead (Luballoy coated)

Taurus 608 has a 4" ported barrel and target sights.

Well over $200 worth of US factory manufactured ammunition included for FREE.

The Taurus is beat to hell, but the frame is not cracked or bent and the timing is fine. I can put all 8 rounds in a playing card at 30 feet, and I'm a lousy shot. Shoots tight groups. I fired 100 rounds of full strength 357 ammo through it and it did not misfire, spit lead, or blow up so I am presenting it as safe to fire.

The rubber monogrip is a little loose. There is some cylinder play but it is not excessive.  Forcing cone is intact. Star is a little worn. This is a great BEATER gun to leave in your cabin, camper, or truck. It is reliable, and it does not matter if it gets dinged up. I do not know how much life is left in it, but it is probably fine for another 300+ rounds. This is a BEATER backup gun for you to stow somewhere and forget about until it is needed. Too damn heavy to carry, in my opinion.

Will swap for a Makarov or a Star 9mm.

Available for sale FTF in the Denver Metro area. CASH ONLY

MUST HAVE CO DL OR CCW AND BE LEGAL TO OWN A HANDGUN IN CO.

Stainless steel Colt Officers ACP with black walnut grips.

45 ACP -- the stainless version can fire +P ammunition, although it is not recommended.

This is probably my favorite pistol, but it is not lefty-friendly, it is heavier than I like, and the recoil out of the 3.5" barrel is more than I care for. Love this pistol, but it does not suit me well enough so it is up for sale.

50 rds Winchester SXZ Personal Protection Lubalox HP

This Stainless Officers Model is in excellent condition, and I've fired about 200 rounds of assorted ammo with only a single FTF, which was a Speer Gold Dot HP with exposed soft lead at the tip, so don't carry it with Gold Dots. Golden Sabers run great.

Prior owner purchased this new in 1984, fired a single box of ammo through it, and left it in his nightstand for the next 25 years. title: For Sale:  erma rx22/ iver johnson tp22 PARTS/REPAIR
postcontent:
Erma RX-22 is the same gun as the American Arms PX22 and the Iver Johnson TP-22.

This pistol was bought new by my grandmother in the 1970s and kept under her pillow for years.  I don't think that she ever fired it.  It came to me and I cleaned it well and have used it for target plinking.  It is a really great gun. This gun consistently shot very tight groups.

Problem with this gun.  
On my last time shooting this pistol, I could not find normal .22 ammunition and bought a brand name high-power load.  I cleaned the gun well, and the first 20 shots or so were perfect, but then it was not so perfect. 

To the best of my understanding of the incident (last month), the round did not fully seat (maybe the shell casing was oversize?), preventing the action from locking down fully. The result was an open breach detonation of the cartridge. This does happen with hand loaded rounds, but seldom with new factory rounds.  

I had the gun inspected by a gunsmith and he recommended changing the barrel, because it may be out of spec and that is why the shell would not lock down. There was no damage to the shooter, but the incident was a shock.  
The gun is intact, with no broken parts or visible metal damage, but I am selling it for repair or parts only.  Warning:  this gun had a mis-fire shell in it and is not guaranteed to be in perfect working condition.

Included: ERMA RX-22, one magazine, an Iver Johnson TP-22 user manual.
Price:  $75.00. Local pickup in Alabama unless by personal arrangement, such as shipping via FFL.

If you have questions, please contact me.

Jon 


Recent auctions of this pistol: www.gunbroker.com/

3 1/2" Barrel, 6 1/4" Overall, 23oz, Blued Steel Construction, Fixed Post Front Sight,  8 round Magazine, Combat Style Hammer, European Magazine Release, Slide Mounted Safety / Decocker, Checkered Composite Grips. Condition (other than noted above): Very Good.
